The discovery raises new questions about whether pets can contract the virus, and if it is contagious from pets (or zoo animals) to humans.
The zoo believes that a caretaker with novel coronavirus infected the cats before developing any symptoms.
This is the first known coronavirus infection of an animal in the United States, and in a tiger anywhere around the world.
Advertisement:Still, pets have tested positive for the coronavirus, albeit on other continents.
There is no evidence that suggests humans are getting the coronavirus from cats, or any pets.